chargeHist.descr: Throw/Discharge Bodily Fluid at Public Safety Worker

result.execSummary:
The defendant Kim L. Lewis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Throw/Discharge Bodily Fluid at Public Safety Worker, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.375(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay restitution in the amount of $717.89 and restitution surcharge. 
------------------------------

Pay court costs.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
------------------------------

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess work release funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
------------------------------

No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  No alcohol.
------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.  The defendant must pay Department of Corrections Supervision fees.  Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
-----------------------------------

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.
------------------------------

9:36 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
DA Zeke S Wiedenfeld appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Probation Agent Joe Befi appeared.  Defendant Kim L. Lewis appeared.   
Matter is on today for a probation review hearing.  
Record is made that the restitution has been paid in full.  It was paid from the defendant's cash bail at the time of sentencing but was likely not reflected on the Assessment Report that DOC received.  The current balance owed is only for Court costs in the amount of $57.78.  Mr. Lewis says he can pay that balance today.  Court directs him to pay the balance to the Clerk of Court's office today.  Defendant's probation will be allowed to discharge on his current discharge date.
Probation review hearing on October 25, 2017 at 09:30 am.
